APPLE'S 80-COLUMN TEXT CARD HASALWAYS CARRIED PRINTED WARNINGS THATTHE CARD SHOULD BE DEACTIVATED IFYOU WANT TO DIRECT OUTPUT TO THEPRINTER. FAILURETO SHUT DOWN THE CARD; ACCORDING TOAPPLE; WILL CAUSE UNPREDICTABLERESULTS AND CONFUSING DISPLAYS.THESE PROBLEMS OCCUR BECAUSE THESOFT SWITCHES ARE NOTRESET PROPERLY BY A PR#0 COMMAND.'PRODOS.PRINT' (CREATED BY THE'PRODOS.PRINT.S' PROGRAM) SOLVESTHIS PROBLEM. BLOAD PRODOS.PRINTINTO MEMORY AND ACTIVATE THE80-COLUMN CARD WITH A PR#3 COMMAND.TO DIRECT OUTPUTTO THE PRINTER; USE 'CALL 768'. TOSEND OUTPUT BACK TO THE 80-COLUMNSCREEN; USE 'CALL 790'.